WEBVTT

00:00:04.630 --> 00:00:09.802
Is the destiny of mankind controlled
by some transcendental entity or Law?

00:00:10.803 --> 00:00:13.806
Is it like the hand of
God hovering above?

00:00:14.932 --> 00:00:16.642
At least it is true...

00:00:17.143 --> 00:00:20.771
...that man has no
control, even over his own will.

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:28.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

00:00:32.908 --> 00:00:34.660
Can't we go any faster?

00:00:35.036 --> 00:00:35.661
No.

00:00:35.786 --> 00:00:38.039
Any faster and it'll
be too much for Griffith.

00:00:40.708 --> 00:00:42.209
They're catching up.

00:01:02.813 --> 00:01:04.815
<i>Feel no shame about shape.</i>

00:01:04.940 --> 00:01:06.776
<i>Weather changes the phrase.</i>

00:01:06.942 --> 00:01:10.446
<i>Even mother will
show you another way.</i>

00:01:10.696 --> 00:01:12.907
<i>So, put your glasses on.</i>

00:01:13.032 --> 00:01:14.950
<i>Nothing will be wrong.</i>

00:01:15.076 --> 00:01:17.161
<i>There's no blame, there's no fame.</i>

00:01:17.328 --> 00:01:18.954
<i>It's up to you.</i>

00:01:19.205 --> 00:01:22.666
<i>The first words should be found.</i>

00:01:23.334 --> 00:01:26.212
<i>Whatever holds you back.</i>

00:01:27.046 --> 00:01:27.671
<i>I...</i>

00:01:28.047 --> 00:01:28.714
<i>... can...</i>

00:01:28.839 --> 00:01:30.925
<i>I can get it off.</i>

00:01:31.092 --> 00:01:31.967
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:32.176 --> 00:01:32.927
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:33.094 --> 00:01:34.720
<i>Tell me what you want.</i>

00:01:34.970 --> 00:01:35.930
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:36.097 --> 00:01:36.847
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:36.972 --> 00:01:38.849
<i>I don't know why you are afraid.</i>

00:01:39.100 --> 00:01:39.975
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:40.184 --> 00:01:40.976
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:41.227 --> 00:01:42.603
<i>Tell me what you'd say.</i>

00:01:42.937 --> 00:01:43.979
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:44.188 --> 00:01:45.106
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:45.231 --> 00:01:45.856
<i>Too late...</i>

00:01:45.981 --> 00:01:47.483
<i>It's too late.</i>

00:01:52.613 --> 00:01:56.617
Eve of the Feast

00:02:03.374 --> 00:02:05.209
First unit, continue pursuit!

00:02:05.251 --> 00:02:06.752
Second unit, follow my lead!

00:02:06.877 --> 00:02:07.753
To the valley!

00:02:19.640 --> 00:02:21.433
At this rate they'll
catch up with us any second!

00:02:21.559 --> 00:02:22.434
We have no choice!

00:02:22.560 --> 00:02:23.686
Should we attack?

00:02:23.936 --> 00:02:25.396
No, we'll make it!

00:02:35.447 --> 00:02:38.200
We thought we'd welcome
you with bows and arrows.

00:02:38.450 --> 00:02:40.161
I'm counting on
you to look after Griffith.

00:02:40.452 --> 00:02:42.204
We'll take good care of him, Big Sister.

00:02:43.831 --> 00:02:46.083
We must annihilate
them here and now, at once!

00:02:48.335 --> 00:02:49.086
Bastards!

00:02:49.211 --> 00:02:50.212
Charge!

00:03:06.854 --> 00:03:07.688
What happened?

00:03:16.864 --> 00:03:17.990
Stop right there!

00:03:25.998 --> 00:03:26.749
Bastard!

00:03:26.999 --> 00:03:27.875
Don't move.

00:03:29.627 --> 00:03:32.129
Now slowly put your
weapons down and surrender!

00:03:36.008 --> 00:03:40.888
You thought you could resurrect
the Hawks by bringing him back.

00:03:42.389 --> 00:03:43.224
Stop it!

00:03:43.515 --> 00:03:44.266
Behold!

00:03:48.354 --> 00:03:50.773
This man will never fight again!

00:03:51.398 --> 00:03:54.109
He will never ride a
horse, nor hold a sword again...

00:03:54.652 --> 00:03:58.239
Why, he can't even
stand on his own two feet!

00:04:01.492 --> 00:04:03.118
You've made a great mistake.

00:04:03.244 --> 00:04:07.039
There is not a single
shred of hope left for any of you.

00:05:12.271 --> 00:05:18.402
What he said about Griffith and the Band
of the Hawk is just a load of bullshit, right?

00:05:22.197 --> 00:05:24.700
Screw you guys, I'll ask him myself.

00:05:24.908 --> 00:05:26.160
You can't do that.

00:05:26.285 --> 00:05:27.411
What do you mean?

00:05:27.911 --> 00:05:30.414
Griffith can't give you an answer.

00:05:32.833 --> 00:05:34.668
You've got to be kidding.

00:05:34.793 --> 00:05:38.088
So his throat got a
little dry living in prison?

00:05:38.297 --> 00:05:39.173
And that's why...

00:05:51.477 --> 00:05:55.105
What the hell!

00:05:55.564 --> 00:05:57.733
This is supposed to
be our new beginning!

00:05:57.941 --> 00:06:01.612
We were going to make a fresh start
after we rescued Griffith, am I wrong?

00:06:02.112 --> 00:06:06.825
For a year we've been living like insects
squirming around, we've lost half our men...

00:06:07.326 --> 00:06:12.081
But despite everything, we all believed
that if we could only get Griffith back...

00:06:12.831 --> 00:06:14.625
Is this it?

00:06:19.129 --> 00:06:23.509
You know, I had a feeling it'd turn out
like this, that something like this would...

00:06:24.510 --> 00:06:25.719
...but...

00:06:27.137 --> 00:06:28.847
...but even so...

00:06:43.529 --> 00:06:44.780
What are we going to do?

00:06:46.532 --> 00:06:49.535
What on earth are we going to do now?

00:06:53.038 --> 00:06:55.666
It's not as if the Band of
Hawk has been annihilated!

00:06:55.874 --> 00:06:57.418
And we have you, Caska...

00:06:57.543 --> 00:06:59.628
Griffith leads the Band of the Hawk.

00:07:00.045 --> 00:07:02.381
You all should know that.

00:07:02.506 --> 00:07:04.258
Yeah, but if that's the...

00:07:04.383 --> 00:07:07.678
Over this past year, Caska's
been through more than anyone else.

00:07:07.886 --> 00:07:09.555
Don't be demanding, give her a break.

00:07:09.763 --> 00:07:10.806
Yeah, but...

00:07:11.181 --> 00:07:12.307
What about us...

00:07:15.561 --> 00:07:16.562
Please give me...

00:07:17.312 --> 00:07:18.439
...some time.

00:07:19.523 --> 00:07:22.526
We still have time
until the others join us.

00:07:23.318 --> 00:07:25.571
Let me think this over until then.

00:07:37.207 --> 00:07:38.083
Hey, wait up!

00:07:39.209 --> 00:07:40.544
What is there to think over?

00:07:40.711 --> 00:07:41.962
What you are you planning?

00:07:42.296 --> 00:07:43.547
You're not thinking of continuing to...

00:07:44.089 --> 00:07:44.840
What were you...

00:07:44.965 --> 00:07:46.967
...about to say back there?

00:07:48.469 --> 00:07:51.221
To keep your promise...

00:07:51.346 --> 00:07:52.848
Just that it's best to
finish what you started...

00:07:53.724 --> 00:07:55.684
You're strong, aren't you?

00:07:57.728 --> 00:08:01.940
Finish what you started,
because you began it yourself...

00:08:04.359 --> 00:08:07.988
Do you really think you
can say that line to Griffith?

00:08:11.742 --> 00:08:13.118
Everyone is weak.

00:08:14.244 --> 00:08:16.705
So we cling to others
and our hopes and dreams.

00:08:18.081 --> 00:08:20.125
In a kind word of comfort...

00:08:20.501 --> 00:08:22.002
Or a strict command...

00:08:26.381 --> 00:08:30.260
I yearned for someone close to me...

00:08:43.190 --> 00:08:45.442
I'll go check on Griffith.

00:08:54.701 --> 00:08:56.828
Griffith, let's change your bandages.

00:08:58.080 --> 00:09:00.457
Whether it's a good
dream or a bad dream...

00:09:00.916 --> 00:09:03.961
No one feels good when
you wake up in the middle of one...

00:09:04.795 --> 00:09:09.049
So, are you going back to traveling
and perfecting your combat skills?

00:09:09.550 --> 00:09:12.094
I guess, and you?

00:09:12.719 --> 00:09:14.096
Well...

00:09:14.805 --> 00:09:18.725
Perhaps I'll bring along the guys that
are left behind and form a band of thieves.

00:09:19.101 --> 00:09:22.563
That way, at least one
of us can look after Griffith...

00:09:22.688 --> 00:09:23.605
I'll come too.

00:09:24.231 --> 00:09:26.567
You already left us once, remember?

00:09:26.692 --> 00:09:28.360
You have no obligation
to stick with us any longer.

00:09:29.361 --> 00:09:30.237
But...

00:09:31.113 --> 00:09:32.072
...you do?

00:09:33.865 --> 00:09:34.825
Well, yeah...

00:09:34.992 --> 00:09:36.243
I'll always be a Hawk.

00:09:36.994 --> 00:09:38.620
But you're different.

00:09:38.996 --> 00:09:42.249
You've already begun
fighting your own battles.

00:09:43.125 --> 00:09:45.627
Leave behind those
who can no longer stand up.

00:09:45.752 --> 00:09:47.504
That's the law of the battlefield, isn't it?

00:09:48.755 --> 00:09:50.507
But that aside...

00:09:51.216 --> 00:09:53.760
You better be sure to
take Caska with you this time.

00:09:55.637 --> 00:09:58.515
She is much too earnest to be
leading a pack of stinking thieves.

00:09:59.766 --> 00:10:01.768
I can't be a thief and have a conscience.

00:10:01.893 --> 00:10:02.519
No thanks!

00:10:03.145 --> 00:10:04.229
I mean it.

00:10:04.354 --> 00:10:06.106
Take her with you,
even if you have to drag her.

00:10:06.773 --> 00:10:07.608
Commander!

00:10:07.733 --> 00:10:08.650
Commander Guts!

00:10:09.776 --> 00:10:13.739
Hey, are you planning on leaving us
without saying a word like last time?

00:10:14.406 --> 00:10:16.992
If you go, please let us go with you!

00:10:17.618 --> 00:10:19.661
We've all talked it over and agree...

00:10:19.786 --> 00:10:21.288
Not one of us disagrees.

00:10:22.873 --> 00:10:23.665
You guys...

00:10:24.041 --> 00:10:25.375
As long as you're here...

00:10:25.417 --> 00:10:27.127
We'll make it through, somehow.

00:10:27.252 --> 00:10:27.794
Commander!

00:10:28.170 --> 00:10:29.630
Please take us with you...

00:10:29.921 --> 00:10:30.547
Commander...

00:10:30.672 --> 00:10:31.632
Please, Commander...

00:10:37.929 --> 00:10:39.181
Perhaps...

00:10:39.514 --> 00:10:41.558
...this has been my home all along.

00:10:44.311 --> 00:10:47.439
I didn't realize it
until this very moment...

00:10:48.523 --> 00:10:51.693
Everything I wanted back
then is right before me now.

00:10:53.320 --> 00:10:54.196
Why?

00:10:55.447 --> 00:10:57.949
Why do I never realize
what I have until it's lost?

00:11:16.093 --> 00:11:17.719
Griffith's hands...

00:11:18.970 --> 00:11:20.931
I never realized how small they were...

00:11:22.224 --> 00:11:25.185
He tried to grasp
everything with these two hands...

00:11:27.229 --> 00:11:29.231
Just by placing his
hand on my shoulder...

00:11:29.856 --> 00:11:31.983
...he made my fears subside...

00:11:33.068 --> 00:11:35.696
He saved me time after time...

00:11:39.116 --> 00:11:41.868
Now I must do the same for him.

00:11:45.622 --> 00:11:46.373
Oh...

00:11:49.084 --> 00:11:50.085
Um...

00:11:50.460 --> 00:11:52.713
Um, I...

00:11:54.381 --> 00:11:55.382
Sorry...

00:11:55.590 --> 00:11:57.384
I'll go get more bandages...

00:11:59.886 --> 00:12:01.596
Griffith, st...

00:12:28.165 --> 00:12:28.790
Hey...

00:12:31.376 --> 00:12:32.294
How's Griffith?

00:12:32.794 --> 00:12:34.671
He just fell asleep...

00:12:35.130 --> 00:12:36.631
Something wrong?

00:12:38.133 --> 00:12:39.801
No, nothing's wrong...

00:12:41.762 --> 00:12:43.680
What the hell's going on?

00:12:44.306 --> 00:12:45.891
No, really, it's nothing!

00:12:46.183 --> 00:12:47.934
So you're crying over nothing?

00:12:48.268 --> 00:12:49.770
Did something happen to Griffith?

00:12:49.895 --> 00:12:50.812
No stop!

00:12:51.813 --> 00:12:52.939
It's not that!

00:12:53.398 --> 00:12:54.149
Hey...

00:12:57.068 --> 00:12:57.944
I'm sorry...

00:12:58.945 --> 00:12:59.821
I can't leave...

00:13:00.071 --> 00:13:00.947
What?

00:13:02.073 --> 00:13:04.451
I-I can't go with you...

00:13:06.661 --> 00:13:07.954
Griffith...

00:13:08.288 --> 00:13:09.831
...he's so small...

00:13:10.582 --> 00:13:12.042
...and he's so frail...

00:13:12.918 --> 00:13:16.046
When he used to be
so proud and confident...

00:13:17.172 --> 00:13:18.465
I can't leave him behind...

00:13:19.174 --> 00:13:21.468
I can't leave him like that...

00:13:23.970 --> 00:13:24.721
I'm sorry...

00:13:25.847 --> 00:13:26.723
I'll stay...

00:13:27.933 --> 00:13:28.433
...as well.

00:13:31.061 --> 00:13:33.063
You have your own
battle to fight, remember?

00:13:33.980 --> 00:13:36.233
You said you were finished
fulfilling other people's dreams.

00:13:38.860 --> 00:13:40.320
You have to <i>go...</i>

00:13:41.863 --> 00:13:44.241
If you're Griffith's true friend...

00:13:44.741 --> 00:13:45.826
...then you must leave...

00:13:47.869 --> 00:13:49.579
...even if you're alone...

00:14:15.146 --> 00:14:17.649
What are you doing
here, trembling with fear?

00:14:43.508 --> 00:14:44.426
Let's go...

00:14:48.054 --> 00:14:49.806
We still have time to play...

00:14:54.185 --> 00:14:55.896
The sun's not down yet.

00:15:16.708 --> 00:15:17.459
Griffith!

00:15:17.709 --> 00:15:19.210
But how?

00:15:19.961 --> 00:15:21.546
Did he hear us?

00:15:21.671 --> 00:15:22.672
I'll go after him!

00:15:23.965 --> 00:15:25.592
Go tell the others!

00:15:41.733 --> 00:15:44.861
I've rested too long...

00:15:45.362 --> 00:15:46.738
It's time to go...

00:15:47.364 --> 00:15:50.075
It's not over yet...

00:15:50.867 --> 00:15:55.121
As long as that cobblestone
path keeps leading me on...

00:16:03.880 --> 00:16:04.881
Griffith...

00:16:05.632 --> 00:16:06.633
Griffith...

00:16:09.511 --> 00:16:10.637
Supper's ready.

00:16:11.137 --> 00:16:12.764
Oh, were you asleep?

00:16:12.889 --> 00:16:13.890
Sorry...

00:16:14.391 --> 00:16:16.643
...but we need to get some air in here...

00:16:17.268 --> 00:16:18.144
Where am I?

00:16:18.395 --> 00:16:19.145
What?

00:16:19.354 --> 00:16:21.606
Is there something on my face?

00:16:22.399 --> 00:16:24.859
You were dreaming about
the old days again, weren't you?

00:16:26.653 --> 00:16:27.487
A dream...

00:16:28.738 --> 00:16:30.532
I see, that's all it was.

00:16:30.782 --> 00:16:34.786
It's been a while since any
of the guys came by to see us.

00:16:34.911 --> 00:16:36.496
I wonder what they're all up to?

00:16:38.540 --> 00:16:41.793
I wonder if that guy's still swinging
his big sword around somewhere?

00:16:43.670 --> 00:16:49.009
The past feels like nothing
more than a dream now.

00:16:50.927 --> 00:16:52.137
Hey Guts!

00:16:52.262 --> 00:16:53.638
Leave Pippin alone!

00:16:54.055 --> 00:16:55.181
Go wash your hands!

00:16:55.390 --> 00:16:56.683
Yes mother!

00:16:59.310 --> 00:17:00.812
Many things happened...

00:17:01.062 --> 00:17:03.023
But they're all just
distant memories now.

00:17:04.024 --> 00:17:06.860
I think I'm much more
suited to this lifestyle...

00:17:07.277 --> 00:17:10.280
My life with you and our
boy, just the three of us...

00:17:14.993 --> 00:17:19.289
This kind of peaceful life is not so bad.

00:18:45.125 --> 00:18:49.254
It's called a Behelit,
the Egg of the King.

00:18:49.963 --> 00:18:52.507
The owner of this
necklace is destined to hold the...

00:18:52.632 --> 00:18:55.510
...entire world in his hands,
in exchange for his flesh and blood.

00:18:57.220 --> 00:19:00.265
In exchange for his flesh and blood?

00:19:03.768 --> 00:19:04.978
Griffith...

00:19:05.270 --> 00:19:07.397
...was it really me
who drove you to this?

00:19:07.647 --> 00:19:10.733
Am I responsible for
what has become of you?

00:19:11.276 --> 00:19:12.402
What should I do?

00:19:12.610 --> 00:19:13.778
What do you want me to do?

00:19:14.362 --> 00:19:16.156
What can I do for you now?

00:19:19.909 --> 00:19:20.785
What's that?

00:19:21.119 --> 00:19:22.162
What the...

00:19:26.791 --> 00:19:27.876
A solar eclipse...

00:19:40.805 --> 00:19:42.140
Griffith!

00:19:56.779 --> 00:19:58.072
Stay away!

00:20:00.909 --> 00:20:02.076
Guts!

00:20:22.597 --> 00:20:24.098
What the hell is that?

00:20:24.224 --> 00:20:24.974
Soldiers?

00:20:25.350 --> 00:20:27.435
Can it be the Midland Army?

00:20:27.852 --> 00:20:29.062
I don't know...

00:20:30.230 --> 00:20:31.814
I don't know what it is...

00:20:32.106 --> 00:20:33.691
But it's ominous...

00:20:36.194 --> 00:20:37.570
Griffith!

00:20:38.488 --> 00:20:39.447
Don't come near!

00:20:39.697 --> 00:20:41.366
Griffith!

00:20:41.616 --> 00:20:42.575
Stay away from me!

00:20:43.868 --> 00:20:45.870
If you touch me now...

00:20:46.496 --> 00:20:48.957
If you grab my shoulder now...

00:20:51.209 --> 00:20:52.752
I'll never be able to...

00:20:54.379 --> 00:20:56.381
You and I, we'll never be the same...

00:21:04.138 --> 00:21:05.098
Griffith.

00:22:03.072 --> 00:22:05.199
<i>Looking back, the morning comes.</i>

00:22:05.325 --> 00:22:08.828
<i>Don't find your face in your glass.</i>

00:22:10.079 --> 00:22:12.915
<i>Take the moonlight by the tail.</i>

00:22:13.041 --> 00:22:15.835
<i>It's a rainy sight that you're shading.</i>

00:22:17.587 --> 00:22:19.088
<i>What is that?</i>

00:22:19.213 --> 00:22:20.423
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:22:20.548 --> 00:22:23.593
<i>What is trying on your crown?</i>

00:22:24.844 --> 00:22:27.722
<i>I'm spending my
glass and walking back.</i>

00:22:27.847 --> 00:22:31.100
<i>So wear my glass, you're fading.</i>

00:22:31.434 --> 00:22:34.729
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:35.104 --> 00:22:38.066
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:38.733 --> 00:22:41.736
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:42.695 --> 00:22:45.448
<i>I'm waiting...</i>

00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:08.888
Next Episode

00:23:11.224 --> 00:23:13.267
Their final destination is darkness...

00:23:13.518 --> 00:23:15.269
And waiting for them is despair.

00:23:16.396 --> 00:23:17.480
They are swarmed by...

00:23:17.772 --> 00:23:18.523
Betrayal...

00:23:19.107 --> 00:23:20.149
...confusion...

00:23:20.525 --> 00:23:21.109
...tears...

00:23:21.859 --> 00:23:22.902
...woe...

00:23:23.403 --> 00:23:24.278
...solitude...

00:23:24.987 --> 00:23:28.366
And all that is left in the end...

00:23:29.158 --> 00:23:30.785
Is the purest dream...

00:23:33.913 --> 00:23:36.916
The Great Eclipse

00:23:37.305 --> 00:24:37.292
